I COULD HAVE MY PICTURES.

19:30.952 --> 19:33.781
-GO AHEAD, PRESS MY
ELBOW. PRESS IT RIGHT HERE.

19:40.179 --> 19:41.484
-THANKS.

19:41.615 --> 19:42.659
-HEY, NEXT TIME YOU'RE
IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD,

19:42.790 --> 19:44.052
STOP BY AND SAY HI.

19:44.183 --> 19:46.272
SEE THAT, THAT'S MY
PLACE RIGHT THERE.

19:46.402 --> 19:49.492
THE SECOND BOX LEFT
OF THE CENTRAL PILLAR.

19:49.623 --> 19:51.581
WE'LL SEE YOU KID.

19:51.712 --> 19:55.063
-ALL RIGHT, SEE YA.
THANKS A LOT.

19:56.064 --> 20:01.374
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

20:16.389 --> 20:18.391
-I'M GONNA MISS THIS PLACE.

20:47.246 --> 20:48.856
-I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

20:49.944 --> 20:51.598
-WAS THIS REALLY NECESSARY?

20:51.728 --> 20:54.209
-I JUST DIDN'T WANT YOU TO
COME WALKING IN ON RILEY AND ME.

20:54.340 --> 20:57.517
-RILEY? WHO'S RILEY?
DO I KNOW HIM?

20:57.647 --> 20:59.475
-NO YOU DON'T, HE'S
AN OCEANOGRAPHER

20:59.606 --> 21:00.824
I'M GOING OUT WITH TOMORROW.

21:00.955 --> 21:02.261
-THEN WHY IS HE HERE TONIGHT?

21:02.391 --> 21:03.392
-I'M GOING OUT TO THE
FAULT WITH HIM TOMORROW

21:03.523 --> 21:05.133
TO PLANT THE SEISMOMETER.

21:05.264 --> 21:07.396
WE'RE GOING OVER THE
GAME PLAN TONIGHT.

21:07.527 --> 21:09.920
-IF YOU'RE JUST GOING
OVER A GAME PLAN TONIGHT

21:10.051 --> 21:11.792
THEN WHY ARE YOU SO WORRIED
ABOUT ME WALKING IN ON YOU?

21:11.922 --> 21:14.403
-BECAUSE WE'RE IN THAT
TRANSITIONAL MODE THAT OCCURS

21:14.534 --> 21:16.666
SPONTANEOUSLY WHEN TWO
PEOPLE DISCOVER THEY HAVE

21:16.797 --> 21:19.016
A LOT IN COMMON AND THEIR
WORKING RELATIONSHIP

21:19.147 --> 21:21.976
STARTS TO DEVELOP
INTO SOMETHING ELSE.

21:22.106 --> 21:23.847
-WELL IF IT'S SO SPONTANEOUS,

21:23.978 --> 21:25.501
THEN WHY DO YOU NEED A POST-IT?

21:25.632 --> 21:28.025
-LOOK, IT'S SPONTANEOUS FOR
HIM OKAY, SO JUST COME IN,

21:28.156 --> 21:29.897
SAY HI NICE TO MEET
YOU AND GOODNIGHT.

21:30.027 --> 21:31.159
-OKAY.

21:31.290 --> 21:32.378
-DO NOT ENGAGE HIM
IN CONVERSATION,

21:32.508 --> 21:34.118
DO NOT DO ANYTHING DISTRACTING.

21:34.249 --> 21:35.468
-FINE.

21:45.739 --> 21:47.262
HI.
-RILEY: HEY.

21:48.002 --> 21:50.221
-RILEY, THIS IS CJ. CJ, RILEY.

21:50.352 --> 21:52.615
-CJ, YOU MUST BE
STEPHANIE'S ROOMMATE.

21:52.746 --> 21:54.400
-IT IS SO NICE TO MEET YOU.

21:54.530 --> 21:55.357
-WELL IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU.

21:55.488 --> 21:56.924
-[THROAT CLEARING]

21:57.881 --> 21:59.013
-OH, GOODNIGHT.

21:59.143 --> 22:00.231
-GOODNIGHT.

22:03.365 --> 22:04.932
-GOODNIGHT.

22:08.979 --> 22:11.112
SO, WHERE WERE WE?

22:11.242 --> 22:13.375
-I BELIEVE WE'RE ON BREATHING
TECHNIQUES WEREN'T WE?

22:13.506 --> 22:16.509
-OH YEAH, FOR FREE DIVING.

22:17.031 --> 22:18.946
AND WHAT WAS THAT PATTERN AGAIN?

22:20.034 --> 22:21.731
TWO IN AND FIVE OUT?

22:21.862 --> 22:23.385
-NO, IT'S TWO IN AND FOUR OUT.

22:23.516 --> 22:24.778
-OH.

22:24.908 --> 22:27.302
-YOU READY?
-MM-HMM.

22:28.085 --> 22:29.348
-INHALE.

22:30.218 --> 22:32.438
-NO, GUYS COME ON,
THIS IS NOT WORKING.

22:32.568 --> 22:33.830
-OUR TIMING'S ALL OFF.

22:33.961 --> 22:35.441
-HEY DON'T LOOK AT ME,
HOBIE KEEPS FALLING BEHIND.

22:35.571 --> 22:37.225
-THAT'S BECAUSE JB'S
PLAYING BEHIND THE BEAT.

22:37.356 --> 22:38.835
-YOU WANT A FASTER BEAT?

22:49.977 --> 22:51.457
-EARTHQUAKE!

22:51.587 --> 22:56.244
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

22:56.375 --> 23:01.815
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

23:17.178 --> 23:18.658
-DID THE EARTH JUST MOVE?

23:20.268 --> 23:21.661
-I THINK IT DID.

23:22.923 --> 23:25.795
-DO YOU THINK ANYONE ELSE
FELT IT, OR WAS IT JUST US?

23:26.883 --> 23:28.276
-I HAVE NO IDEA.

23:30.931 --> 23:32.411
-EXCUSE ME.

23:38.547 --> 23:40.593
I JUST CAME IN TO
GET A FLASHLIGHT.

23:40.723 --> 23:42.551
IN CASE THERE'S ANOTHER QUAKE.

23:42.682 --> 23:44.074
IGNORE ME.

23:48.601 --> 23:49.950
KEEP DANCING.

23:52.474 --> 23:54.389
-COULD YOU JUST EXCUSE
ME FOR ONE MOMENT?

23:54.520 --> 23:55.608
-YEAH.

24:00.134 --> 24:01.352
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

24:01.483 --> 24:02.832
-WELL IN CASE
THERE'S ANOTHER QUAKE

24:02.963 --> 24:04.791
I'M NOT GONNA GO RUNNING OUT
OF HERE JUST WEARING THIS.

24:04.921 --> 24:06.314
-OH, BUT YOU CAN GO
RUNNING OUT OF HERE

24:06.445 --> 24:08.011
JUST WEARING THAT IN
FRONT OF A TOTAL STRANGER?

24:08.142 --> 24:09.796
-WELL HE WOULDN'T BE
A TOTAL STRANGER IF YOU

24:09.926 --> 24:12.320
WOULD HAVE BEEN POLITE ENOUGH
TO INTRODUCE US PROPERLY.

24:12.451 --> 24:13.495
-ME, POLITE?

24:13.626 --> 24:14.844
DO YOU THINK IT'S POLITE

24:14.975 --> 24:16.324
TO WALK IN ON US
WEARING A NEGLIGEE?

24:16.455 --> 24:18.152
-THIS COVERS MORE
THAN A BATHING SUIT.

24:18.282 --> 24:20.110
-IT HAS A TOTALLY
DIFFERENT CONNOTATION.

24:20.241 --> 24:23.026
-CJ: DON'T BE SILLY,
YOU'RE BEING RIDICULOUS.

24:27.596 --> 24:29.729
-I'M SORRY, I
REMEMBERED THE BATTERIES

24:29.859 --> 24:32.558
IN THE FLASHLIGHT WERE LOW AND
I DIDN'T WANT HER TO GET--
-[KNOCKING]

24:32.688 --> 24:34.168
WHAT NOW?

24:35.474 --> 24:36.997
I GOT IT.

24:40.914 --> 24:43.351
-HI.
-CAROLINE.

24:44.700 --> 24:46.528
CAROLINE, WHAT'S WRONG?

24:47.529 --> 24:50.401
-OH GOSH, OH GOD
THIS IS A BAD TIME.

24:50.532 --> 24:52.186
YOU KNOW WHAT, I'LL COME BACK.
-OH NO, NO.

24:52.316 --> 24:53.361
-CAROLINE: I'LL COME BACK
ANOTHER TIME, IT'S OKAY.

24:53.492 --> 24:55.711
-CAROLINE, WHAT'S GOING ON?

24:57.191 --> 24:59.323
-FRANK AND I ARE
GETTING A DIVORCE.

24:59.454 --> 25:00.716
-CJ: OH.
-STEPHANIE: OH, CAROLINE.

25:01.195 --> 25:02.588
-CJ: I HOPE YOU'RE OKAY.

25:02.718 --> 25:04.198
I'M GLAD YOU CAME HERE.

25:06.809 --> 25:07.897
-HEY LOOK, IT'S GETTING LATE.

25:08.028 --> 25:09.377
WE GOTTA GET A
REALLY EARLY START.

25:09.508 --> 25:10.683
GET SOME SLEEP.

25:10.813 --> 25:12.075
-I'LL TRY.

25:14.121 --> 25:15.688
-I REALLY ENJOYED TONIGHT.

25:15.818 --> 25:17.167
-ME TOO.

25:21.302 --> 25:24.000
-CJ, IT WAS A
PLEASURE MEETING YOU.

25:24.653 --> 25:27.264
CAROLINE, I HOPE
THINGS WORK OUT FOR YA.
-THANKS.

25:27.395 --> 25:30.529
-GOODNIGHT.
-STEPHANIE: GOODNIGHT.

25:33.923 --> 25:35.534
CAROLINE--
-WELL HE SEEMED REALLY NICE.

25:35.664 --> 25:36.447
WHO WAS HE?

25:36.578 --> 25:38.406
-CAROLINE, LOOK, WHAT HAPPENED?

25:39.581 --> 25:41.148
-FRANK CHEATED ON ME AGAIN.

25:42.062 --> 25:44.281
BUT THIS TIME I HAD
THE GUTS TO LEAVE HIM.

25:44.760 --> 25:48.372
SO, I WAS KINDA HOPING I
COULD STAY HERE WITH YOU GUYS

25:48.503 --> 25:50.505
FOR A LITTLE WHILE UNTIL
I FIND A PLACE OF MY OWN.

25:50.636 --> 25:51.854
IS THAT OKAY?

25:52.551 --> 25:53.987
-YEAH.
-OKAY.

25:54.117 --> 25:55.858
-LET'S DO IT ONE MORE TIME,

25:55.989 --> 25:58.252
THIS TIME DO IT
LIKE WE'RE ON MTV.

25:59.862 --> 26:02.125
YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO BE
HOME OVER AN HOUR AGO.

26:06.303 --> 26:08.044
-YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO COME
IN THERE AND DRAG ME OUT.

26:08.175 --> 26:09.437
-LOOK, IF YOU HAD COME HOME

26:09.568 --> 26:10.786
WHEN YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO
I WOULDN'T HAVE HAD TO.

26:10.917 --> 26:13.093
-YEAH SORRY OKAY, WE
GOT INTO THE MUSIC,

26:13.223 --> 26:15.008
I LOST TRACK OF TIME.
-WELL THE MUSIC BETTER BE

26:15.138 --> 26:16.226
THE ONLY THING
YOU'RE GETTING INTO.

26:16.792 --> 26:18.577
-I'M NOT DOING DRUGS
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU MEAN.

26:18.707 --> 26:20.056
-LOOK, WE GOTTA
HAVE A TALK, OKAY?

26:20.187 --> 26:22.842
ABOUT MUSIC, ABOUT PRIORITIES,
ABOUT A LOT OF THINGS.

26:23.451 --> 26:25.801
-I REALLY DON'T WANT
TO TALK RIGHT NOW, OKAY?

26:26.497 --> 26:27.803
-HOBIE.

26:29.152 --> 26:30.110
HOBIE!

26:30.240 --> 26:32.808
AH, PUBERTY.

26:34.331 --> 26:39.815
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

26:53.655 --> 26:54.830
-HEY.

26:55.831 --> 26:56.963
WHAT TIME IS IT?

26:57.093 --> 26:58.573
-IT'S ALMOST THREE
IN THE MORNING.

26:58.704 --> 26:59.879
WHY DON'T YOU GO
SLEEP IN MY BED?

27:00.009 --> 27:03.012
-MM-MM, NO, I
REALLY LIKE IT HERE.

27:04.840 --> 27:07.930
HEY, STEPH, I WAS
THINKING, WITH SUMMER GONE

27:08.061 --> 27:10.193
THAT I COULD GET BACK
INTO SHAPE AND RE-QUALIFY

27:10.324 --> 27:12.805
DURING THE NEXT RECHECK AND
TAKE HER PLACE AT BAYWATCH.

27:12.935 --> 27:15.546
-CAROLINE, YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
A LIFEGUARD SINCE HIGH SCHOOL.

27:15.677 --> 27:18.288
-I KNOW, IT'S JUST THOSE WERE
THE HAPPIEST TIMES, STEPH.

27:18.419 --> 27:20.421
I JUST-- I REALLY
WANNA BE HAPPY AGAIN.

27:20.551 --> 27:21.770
-YOU WILL BE.

27:21.901 --> 27:23.424
I PROMISE YOU WILL BE.

27:25.861 --> 27:31.258
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

27:49.232 --> 27:50.407
-MAN.

27:51.539 --> 27:53.933
I'VE GOTTA GET THAT ON TAPE.

28:22.788 --> 28:27.923
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

30:30.741 --> 30:32.613
-CAREFUL.
-DID YOU GUYS
CHECK OVER THE SEISMOMETER?

30:32.743 --> 30:34.528
-IT'LL BE ONLINE IN A
COUPLE OF SECONDS HERE.

30:40.751 --> 30:46.061
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

31:36.372 --> 31:38.331
-THOSE ULTRA LOW
FREQUENCY RADIO WAVES

31:38.461 --> 31:39.810
ARE GOING RIGHT OFF THE SCALE.

31:39.941 --> 31:41.247
WHAT DO YOU MAKE OF THAT?

31:41.377 --> 31:43.727
-COULD BE A
PRE-TEMPER VIBRATION.

31:43.858 --> 31:47.340
REMEMBER SANTA CRUZ BEFORE
THE LOMA PRIETA QUAKE?

31:47.470 --> 31:49.037
-SO HOW'S HE DOING DOWN THERE?

31:49.168 --> 31:50.299
EVERYTHING IN PLACE?

31:51.126 --> 31:53.215
-YEAH, BUT WE'RE GETTING
SOME VERY UNUSUAL READINGS.

31:53.346 --> 31:55.043
-RILEY?
-RILEY: YEAH.

31:55.174 --> 31:57.611
-CAN YOU REPOSITION
THAT SEISMOMETER?

31:57.741 --> 31:58.829
-RILEY: WHERE DO YOU NEED IT?

31:58.960 --> 32:00.831
-TRY GETTING IT ON BEDROCK.

32:00.962 --> 32:06.141
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

32:16.804 --> 32:19.372
-OH MY GOD!
-STEPHANIE: WHAT?

32:19.502 --> 32:21.722
-RILEY! GET OUT OF THERE!

32:33.255 --> 32:37.520
-[SCREAMING]

33:35.709 --> 33:37.406
-NO!

33:37.537 --> 33:38.842
NO!

33:46.850 --> 33:48.156
-OH MY GOD!

34:02.257 --> 34:04.564
-[SCREAMING]

34:38.293 --> 34:43.646
-[SCREAMING]

34:50.130 --> 34:51.350
-HOBIE!

35:11.761 --> 35:12.849
GOD.

35:14.024 --> 35:15.417
HOBIE?

35:18.507 --> 35:20.683
-CAROLINE: CJ! CJ!

35:20.814 --> 35:21.945
-CAROLINE!

35:22.076 --> 35:24.122
-OH MY GOD, WHAT DO
I DO, WHAT DO I DO?

35:24.252 --> 35:26.515
I'M STUCK IN HERE.
-CJ: HANG ON.

35:27.516 --> 35:29.562
-HELP ME!
-OH, GOD.

35:32.173 --> 35:33.566
EVERYTHING'S GOING TO BE OKAY.

35:33.696 --> 35:38.397
-[SCREAMING]

35:54.195 --> 35:55.153
-WHAT WAS THAT?

35:55.283 --> 35:57.067
-THAT MUST HAVE
BEEN AN AFTERSHOCK.

35:57.198 --> 35:58.678
WE GOTTA GET TO HEADQUARTERS.

36:02.725 --> 36:08.296
-[GASPING]

36:10.385 --> 36:11.865
-OKAY, HOLD ONTO THE BOAT.

36:11.995 --> 36:13.475
HOLD ONTO THE BOAT.

36:18.001 --> 36:19.089
JUST HOLD ON OKAY?

36:19.220 --> 36:20.700
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

36:23.703 --> 36:25.748
HOLD ON, MAX, OKAY?
I'M GONNA GET TOM.

36:26.532 --> 36:28.403
-BUT DON'T LEAVE ME!

36:52.035 --> 36:53.123
-HELP!

36:54.255 --> 36:56.605
PLEASE, SOMEBODY HELP ME!

36:58.128 --> 37:01.610
I'M STUCK, PLEASE, HELP!

37:02.742 --> 37:03.830
OH NO.

37:05.832 --> 37:09.879
-[CREAKING]

37:14.057 --> 37:19.106
-[GRUNTING]

37:20.281 --> 37:21.630
-MAX, HOLD HIM.

37:21.761 --> 37:22.370
-I CAN'T.

37:22.501 --> 37:24.154
-JUST DO IT, MAX.

37:38.604 --> 37:40.649
-COME ON, GUY, COME ON.

37:41.128 --> 37:42.085
THERE YOU GO.

37:42.216 --> 37:43.565
WHAT ABOUT RILEY?

37:44.305 --> 37:45.915
-HOW CLOSE TO THE FAULT WAS HE?

37:46.133 --> 37:47.743
-HE WAS IN IT.

37:49.919 --> 37:55.490
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

38:11.767 --> 38:16.946
-[ENDING THEME MUSIC]
